<br>
Saphron sat in the dingy room thinking. She was thinking not only of Stormygale, but of her own present, past and future. She missed her friends in Natural Selection. Her new friends in The Imperium Knights were wonderful people, to be sure, but they just did not stoke the fires of adventure that had long lain dorman in her soul. She wanted to see the Planes, but felt too tired, or too unneeded, to do so. She knew that her old friends Quaras, Salar and even Temyez had joined the guild that Stormygale had grown to call her new home, the Claw of Nagafen.<br>
<br>
&quot;Athene?&quot; Saphron said to the contemplative druid as she studied her maps.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I feel empty inside. What do you know of the Claw of Nagafen? Do you think they might have a place for a couple of old wayward women like us?&quot; <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:gold;font-family:Garamond;font-size:medium;">Saphron LaFeete</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--> <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:purple;font-family:garamond;font-size:small;">High Priestess of Bristlebane </span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub148.ezboard.com/bthewordsofnagafen.showUserPublicProfile?gid=saphronlafeete>Saphron LaFeete</A> at: 7/19/03 5:58 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#212128><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub148.ezboard.com/bthewordsofnagafen.showUserPublicProfile?gid=athene>Athene</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.mindspring.com/~abvogan/_uimages/ahstarsm.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoN Member</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#7A8798>(7/19/03 7:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=25>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.mindspring.com/~abvogan/eye.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Fraud</span><hr size=1> Athene looked up.  “Funny you should ask, … or are you reading my mind again?”  Athene smiled at her friend of many seasons.  Traveling the lands with Saphron was delightful, even in circumstances so dire.  She might as well just be frank about all the twisting turns her mind had taken since she had left the Ring and set out on her own.  Her eyes glistened, a mixture of humor and sadness.  “After our talk in Rivervale, I thought briefly of trying to revive Natural Selection.  I visited the guild tree—still in good shape, still some good souls there, … but so few.”  Athene’s voice grew wistful, her eyes staring not at Saphron but into the past.  “You could probably tell from some of the messages I sent you over the last few weeks that I was pondering whether it might be possible to bring it all back.  But it’s too late.  It didn’t take me long to see that, and I suppose it’s a blessing that I realized it quickly.”<br>
<br>
Saphron nodded.<br>
<br>
“I’ve exchanged a few messages with Quaras.  He’s mentioned the Claw, though I don’t know how serious he is.  He’s expressed a lot of concern for Stormygale too.  She’s often been gone.  Now that I’ve seen her eye-to-eye—brief though it was--I sense the pain she is feeling is incredibly deep, and I don’t know which is worse for her—the physical injury or the heartache.”<br>
<br>
“Probably a torturous blend of the two.”<br>
<br>
“Aye, I suppose you speak true.  Temyez has left the lands.  Have we spoke of this?  My mind is so muddled I can’t recall.”<br>
<br>
“I knew.  Demitasse, told me.”<br>
<br>
“Ha, … so you have met Demitasse?  In the old guild hall or elsewhere?<br>
<br>
“The guild hall.”  Saphron smiled mischievously.  “Quite something—that dwarven lass.” <br>
<br>
“Indeed.” <br>
<br>
Both chuckled, and then the two women sat silent for a while.  They knew how fond Stormygale had been of Temyez.  His leaving the boundaries of Norrath and Abruzi’s death had occurred within the same year.  Either event would have been difficult to get past, but adding to those sad circumstances was the break up of the council of Natural Selection, which had preceded both.  It had been a year of disappointments for Stormygale.  And her initial delight and excitement after joining the honorable and established guild The Claw of Nagafen had been marred by some physical injury from which she had not recovered.<br>
<br>
“I’m not sure she has totally forgiven me, Saphron, for leaving the guild, for how it all fell out.”  Athene smiled broadly.  “But I know she loves me still.”<br>
<br>
Saphron raised an eyebrow.<br>
<br>
“When she saw me in the inn, she waved.”  Athene nearly cackled.  “Now think had I been a certain dark-elf enchantress.  Think she would have waved?”<br>
<br>
‘Heh, no, … I think I would have been restoring your soul to yer blackened corpse.”<br>
<br>
“Never was a druid more aptly named than that Stormygale, eh?”<br>
<br>
And so, it was more or less decided.  They would seek out the Claw after they brought Stormygale El`Orian home.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#141419><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub148.ezboard.com/bthewordsofnagafen.showUserPublicProfile?gid=stormygalewindrunner>Stormygale Windrunner</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.cpmission.com/graphics/icons/icon45.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoN Member</span><br>  Posts: 865<br> <font color=#7A8798>(7/19/03 11:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Fraud</span><hr size=1> She was throwing pebbles at the far wall. She had nothing better to do, and it helped her think. &quot;can HELP!&quot;  What did Athene mean by that? <br>
<br>
Oh it had all been very clear what Athene had been doing at the inn in her wedding dress. Probably the fanciest robe Athene owned. Lord knows it was beautiful and Athene and Nurul had looked so fine as they took their vows high on the castle overlooking the Twilight Sea. It was clear Athene was going to try to use her finest garment to  wheedle information out of the innkeepers, but they would never have talked. Athene didn't know the password. <br>
<br>
Stormygale then wondered what had happened to that marriage. Had the marriage failed? There was a time when Nurul and Athene could not be parted.  Stormygale hadn't seen the intimidating Nurul in months, and hadn't seen Athene anywhere near him.  And Athene had gone guildless. Left the Ring. Well, Stormygale hoped Athene enjoyed it. She remembered all too clearly how it was to be completely alone. Her guild fallen apart because Athene had decided it would be so. Anger, hate. Loneliness. Followed by the death of her mother and almost immediately following that, the loss of Temyez.<br>
<br>
Temyez. The one person she had always counted on had let her down. He had up and left the world, never to be seen again. She had Athene to thank for that. And while she'd been lucky enough to find a new home in the grand and wonderful Claw of Nagafen, she was now crippled. Useless. Better off dead.  What possible good could she be to a guild who needed active members when she could barely stand to walk?<br>
<br>
She sipped her brandy and threw another pebble. <br>
<br>
She kept thinking of the icy bridge as one entered Thurgadin. She had always wondered what was down there. Maybe it would soon be time to find out. Oh, no levitation. She'd find out the fast way.  One glorious view to appease her curiosity and then she too would be gone. She and her pain. She and her resentment. She and her anger. <br>
<br>
In a morbid way the game of cat and mouse with Saphron and Athene had sparked a bit of life back into her, but it, like everyting else, would fade and become an illusion. The two people she had loved most in this world had left her within weeks of each other. Stormygale had then had the accident with the dragon and the next morning her black raven locks had gone white as snow. <br>
<br>
An icy sign that kept calling to her.<br>
<br>
Soon maybe, eh? Soon... <p><b>Stormygale El`Orian</b><img border=0 src="http://www.cpmission.com/graphics/icons/icon45.gif" /></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#212128><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub148.ezboard.com/bthewordsofnagafen.showUserPublicProfile?gid=saphronlafeete>Saphron LaFeete</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoN Member</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#7A8798>(7/20/03 7:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Fraud</span><hr size=1> Saphron sat atop her white mount, Willow, as they sped across the frozen wastes, hugging close to her both for balance, and for warmth. She had won this mount in an expedition into the Temple of Ssraeshza, and had no idea at the time just how valuable she would become.<br>
<br>
&quot;Quickly, my Willow,&quot; she had murmured to her pony, &quot;We must reach that awful giant city by nightfall.&quot;<br>
<br>
She had gone to Thurgadin on her own, on a hunch, to look for Stormygale. She knew there were some secluded inns, and some even more secluded drinking establishments there. None had seen her friend, but she had overheard talk between a couple of relatively youngish (and quite ale-logged) rangers in one of the seedier bars in the town. They spoke of a white-haired woman traveling on horseback in the &quot;Lands of the Mother&quot; and how she had easily vanquished a mighty panther.<br>
<br>
Saphron knew that Stormygale would not seek out the Plane of Growth, for even she could not stand the Icy Mother of All enough to seek shelter in her plane. Besides, Saphron thought . . . no booze there.<br>
<br>
She had also made sure to seek Tondar out once again before leaving ShadowHaven. She patted the medicine bag he had given her, holding it close to her as if it meant life and death. And . . . she knew it just might.<br>
<br>
Willow traversed the snow-covered crags deftly and quickly, and soon, they had passed through the pass to the Eastern Wastes and were nearing the great canyon to Kael. Saphron shivered, not because she was cold, but because she still did not like to travel through this evil city, even after several seasons of doing so.<br>
<br>
Dismounting outside the city gates, she whispered to Willow, &quot;Rest now, my friend, I'll need you in the Wakening Lands,&quot; and Willow evanesced into vapor. <br>
<br>
Preparing her best mind soothing spell, she prepared herself for the arduous journey through the city of the Frost Giants.  <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:gold;font-family:Garamond;font-size:medium;">Saphron LaFeete</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--> <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:purple;font-family:garamond;font-size:small;">High Priestess of Bristlebane </span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#141419><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub148.ezboard.com/bthewordsofnagafen.showUserPublicProfile?gid=revil>Revil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoN Officer</span><br>  Posts: 1501<br> <font color=#7A8798>(7/20/03 1:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Fraud</span><hr size=1> Slowly creeping into the city of Skyshrine unseen. Revil, hoping to snatch a purse or 2 on his way thru going to Temple of Veeshan hears a pebble hit the wall, and than another. Some alternating patterns of  “tap” than “tap tap”. Getting a grin on his face. He knows for who his first pickpocket of the long drudging day will be. Making sure he stays to the shadows unseen by any of the kin’s lackeys for Revil is not welcome to the great city of Dragon kin since he turned on them long ago. <br>
<br>
“Ah, yes nothing like the fresh warm blood of a dragon to make your toes curl in delight”, he whispers to himself as he sneaks from shadow to shadow. The closer he gets to the pebbles hitting the wall the louder it gets. Like the ringing of a freshly strung up drum getting ready to see it’s first battle of bloodshed. Revil whispers to himself with ever step he gets closer to the archway, “This person must really have problems. I’m not sure whether to feel more sorry for the wall or the pebbles.”<br>
<br>
He slowly moves into position of the archway to take a peek inside. As he is about to scout the surrounds of the room “Whack” a pebble hits him in the forehead. Quickly gathering himself securely around the corner to be sure he won’t be seen. He rubs his forehead wondering if the person inside saw him, or just threw the pebble wildly, and missed the wall completely.<br>
<br>
Quickly thinking, he uses this to his advantage to get into the room, and measure up his first loot of the long tiring day. Revil picks up the pebble that hit him. Slowly creeping into the archway ready for another pebble if it comes. He gets a good view of his surrounds, and analyzes the room for anything he can use to his advantage.<br>
<br>
First thing Revil notices is a beautiful drunk woman. Even though she is a little tipsy while drinking her brandy. Her long white hair shines, and glows with every tilt of her neck. He watches as she slowly stumbles, and crawls to get another pebble to throw at the wall. Her long white hair slowly falls from the top of her head down to her cheek like Felwithe’s finest silk dresses slowly flowing, and swaying around the sleek and slender bodies of the loveliest elven beauties in Norrath.<br>
<br>
Taking peaks out the corner of his eye, not taking his sights off the woman he analyzes the rest of the room. So dull, and empty compared to the sight he sees before himself. Revil mutters so the woman doesn’t hear, “She is too beautiful for this room. There must be a reason why she choose the most dullest, and unentertaining rooms of the kin to set up camp.”<br>
<br>
Noticing he won’t get her attention by just talking to her while hidden. Revil uses the pebble he got hit in the face with to attract her attention, and scare her a bit since she seem off in her own world of thought.<br>
<br>
Revil tosses the pebble as hard as he can against the wall, but making sure he doesn’t hit the woman.<br>
