<br>
She listened so hard it made her ears ring. Or, well, maybe that was the brandy. Finally deciding to act nonchalant, as she was sure someone was there, she sat up and pulled her hair away from her face while she took a sip of her brandy. As she set the bottle down, she slyly realized that she still had her port to Wakening Lands memorized. She could escape anytime she wanted, but first to have some fun with whomever was playing games. She stood and walked to the bed and bent over her packs as a ruse while she incanted &quot;See Invisable&quot; on herself. Her eyes glimmered, but they glimmered while she had her head in a pack. It was highly doubtful it was noticed. <br>
<br>
Then as she had it memorized still, she cast Improved Camo which unfortunately the person in the room with her would be able to see, but there was no helping that. She was fairly certain whoever it was, was in the room, or if not, in the hall directly outside. <br>
<br>
She turned around to see the heels of the little jokester vanishing through the door. So! She did have an intruder! She'd bet good platinum it was a sneaky rogue or someone like that. That heel had been too small for a runter rogue, and not hairy enough. Too small for a human. Maybe a half elf? Well, she'd see.<br>
<br>
She picked up her brandy bottle and sat on the bed, leaning back and getting comfortable against the wall, sipping her brandy and waiting. Surely the little thief would return, not being quite sure if she'd been just refreshing buffs or not. Especially if she made no move to follow and if he or she hadn't actually seen Stormygale disappear.  So she sat and she sipped and unrealizingly got drunker and drunker as she did so, until she closed her eyes one last time and they stayed shut; the half open bottle falling from her hand to lay sideways on the bed, almost, but not quite spilling the remaining contents. Her unconsious body slid sideways over the top of her packs, squashing them a bit but she was out cold and snoring. <p><b>Stormygale El`Orian</b><img border=0 src="http://www.cpmission.com/graphics/icons/icon45.gif" /></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#141419><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub148.ezboard.com/bthewordsofnagafen.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sylvrwolf>SylvrWolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoN Member</span><br>  Posts: 236<br> <font color=#7A8798>(7/21/03 8:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.datamagick.com/images/dancing.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Fraud</span><hr size=1> On her trek through the lands, checking on the various leaders of the dragons, Kalyndria was grateful that she had kept her faction with them friendly. &quot;Though,&quot; she mused, &quot;it won't be that way for long.&quot; Many times throughout the past, she had been taunted by friends and guildmates alike to leave behind the allies she had and join the Giants against them. Up until now, she refused. With a dissapointed sigh for lost friendships and wondering why she chose now to switch sides, she continues on toward her last stop, Skyshrine.<br>
<br>
After porting into Cobalt Scar, she sees a human in a purplish robe trailing sparklies behind her. &quot;Hrm,&quot; she mumbles to herself. &quot;Is that...VANDER! Wait up!&quot; Quickly casting Flight of Eagles on herself, she hurries to catch up with the Necromancer. <br>
<br>
&quot;I wonder what's going on?&quot; Busy with communications with her friends, and not really up to hunting or working her various tradeskills lately, she hadn't really been paying attention to what her guild was talking about. She seemed to remember someone....&quot;By Tunare! How could I have missed that?!&quot;<br>
<br>
Redoubling her efforts to catch the speedy Necromancer, (how in all of Norrath has she gotten so FAST?!) Kalyndria races on to try to be of some assistance. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.users.bigpond.net.au/tamtam/kalyndria3.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
