</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#212128><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub148.ezboard.com/bthewordsofnagafen.showUserPublicProfile?gid=saphronlafeete>Saphron LaFeete</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoN Member</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#7A8798>(7/21/03 9:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Fraud</span><hr size=1> The giants struck quickly. Shards of velium shattered against her back as the mace struck. Thank Bristlebane the dragons of Skyshrine had bestowed her with such strong armor.<br>
<br>
Even so, the diminutive cleric was knocked from her horse. As she slammed into the tree, she saw the tigeraptors racing at full speed.<br>
<br>
&quot;Get to safety!&quot; she screamed to her beloved Willow, who disappeared into the ether immediately.<br>
<br>
Turning, Saphron saw the great Frost Giant Commander lumbering her way, muttering something about ruining his lands. Mustering up all the energy in her broken body, she cast her most powerful stun, and watched as the giant's eyes glazed over. He would be out of commission for a few seconds, anyway. <br>
<br>
Now on her feet, Saphron hobbled toward the dark cave that she knew would harbor some sanctuary. She knew the tigeraptors would not be far behind, unless they had decided to attack the stunned giant. <br>
<br>
No time to think. Just run.<br>
<br>
Somehow she managed to make it to the end of the cave, where the emotionless sentinels gazed at her amiably.<br>
<br>
&quot;Help . . . me . . . &quot; was all she managed before she collapsed at their feet.<br>
<br>
Hard velium arms scooped up the halfling cleric. The sentry waited for the command from his commander.<br>
<br>
&quot;Put her in the room next to the malodorous human. I shall send for one of the drakes to have a look at her. She wears the sacred armor of Akkhirus, and is friend to Veeshan. Treat her as such. When she wakes we shall discover her true intentions.&quot; <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:gold;font-family:Garamond;font-size:medium;">Saphron LaFeete</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--> <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:purple;font-family:garamond;font-size:small;">High Priestess of Bristlebane </span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#141419><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub148.ezboard.com/bthewordsofnagafen.showUserPublicProfile?gid=stormygalewindrunner>Stormygale Windrunner</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.cpmission.com/graphics/icons/icon45.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoN Member</span><br>  Posts: 874<br> <font color=#7A8798>(7/21/03 9:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Fraud</span><hr size=1> Stormygale snorted herself awake. Shaking her head trying to clear it, she tried to remember.... something.  Pebbles... pebbles... A sneak!  <br>
<br>
Forgetting her pain, she quickly checked her belongings. All her stuff was there and she sighed with relief. She had items upon her she would not wish to lose. <br>
<br>
As she checked her coinage she realized she was short 10 platinum pieces. What in the world? That rogue could have stolen her blind and sold her into slavery, and there wouldn't have been a thing she could do about it! <br>
<br>
She sat back against the wall and picked up her brandy bottle and sipped it, as much to clear her mouth as for the ever present pain. And then her eyes lit upon ten gleaming Platinum pieces stacked with care right in the middle of the floor.  Stormygale pondered the platinum for a long while before finally getting up to reclaim her money. She admitted to herself, she was completely stumped this time. A compassionate rogue? Who ever heard of such a thing?<br>
<br>
She would dearly love to tell Quaras of it. But she dared not go near him.  He would surely turn her over to her guild or worse,  and she could almost hear his gravely voice, made furry from all his pipe smoking, saying &quot;It's for your own good, lass.&quot;  Bah! He would never understand that there was nothing that could be done. But there was something she could do, and that was move. It was clear Skyshrine was not as safe as she had thought. But this now posed a pretty problem. Where to go? Where to go? Dragon Necropolis? No. Too busy with people raiding there. <br>
<br>
She began to chuckle. Oh no. It was too funny. Should she? She might be caught by that Athene, but she'd have to take a risk.That rogue had made her too nervous. <br>
<br>
Throwing on her packs, she drained the rest of her bottle and memorized the spell. One she hadn't used in a long time. Incanting the words, she vanished in a puff of little rings of energy.<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p><b>Stormygale El`Orian</b><img border=0 src="http://www.cpmission.com/graphics/icons/icon45.gif" /></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#212128><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub148.ezboard.com/bthewordsofnagafen.showUserPublicProfile?gid=athene>Athene</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.mindspring.com/~abvogan/_uimages/ahstarsm.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoN Member</span><br>  Posts: 80<br> <font color=#7A8798>(7/21/03 1:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=33>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.mindspring.com/~abvogan/eye.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Fraud</span><hr size=1> Athene slid the pages she had been reading across the table.  She was tired.  She rubbed her eyes.  She stretched and looked around.  It was very quiet.  The library in the Plane of Knowledge was large and spacious, yet cozy at the same time.  Some of the levels rarely saw visitors.  The recess she chose was one of these.  She had been reading and writing all afternoon and had not been disturbed.  <br>
<br>
Among the documents over which she had poured was the history of The Claw of Nagafen.  It was an interesting tale, detailing its beginnings in the days when the two greatest living dragons known to man were the Lady Vox and Nagafen.  Some documents were more mundane—lists of current and former members and officers, rules for the division of loot, guidelines for conflict resolution, and others.  One of the most intriguing had been written by the guild’s founder, a scholarly necromancer.  It was titled <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Battle Tactics: The Writings of Sun Tzu</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, annotated by Vandergrave.<br>
<br>
Late in the afternoon, Athene had begun penning her own application to the Claw, but she would not submit it unless she gained Stormygale’s approval—and made sure that Quaras's suggestion that she consider pursuing his guild were serious.  Salar’s name she did not find among the most recent list of members.  They had been close companions in the days following the discovery of Kunark.  But since that time, and her marriage, and the decline of Natural Selection, they had lost contact somewhat.  He had gone on—first to another guild, then to other lands.  She still heard from him occasionally.<br>
<br>
In former days, the guild had communicated by telepathy.  It was not a skill one had to develop in the usual manner.  It was more a matter of being at peace with one’s self and open enough to others to allow their thoughts to pass through.  It was not an ability she’d had as a child; it had come with maturity.  She could remember days long ago when she fought and fished and swam in the vast Karanas—alone, but not really.  Unless she were very harried or deeply absorbed in someone or something, she could often hear the voices of her guildmates shouting their triumphs, expressing their sorrows, giving brief news of the world and the lands in which they traveled.  She was able to respond in kind, sending her thoughts forth where they wended toward those who would hear them.  They didn’t always reach their destination.  One could not intrude one’s thoughts on another who was unreceptive.  In all matters, it was hard to find those who did not wish to be found.<br>
<br>
She tried now with little hope to reach Stormygale wherever she might be.  ~I only want to talk, Stormy.  I think I—I think we—can help.  Won’t you let us try?  Can you hear me, Stormygale?~<br>
<br>
Telepathy was a skill that came most easily to those of very close association.  Sometimes the messages were delayed.  Did they bounce off the world’s edges like echoes?  Athene didn’t know.  She did know nearly a month before she had heard the voice of Abruzi urging Athene to help her daughter.  Saphron had heard it too.  But Abruzi was dead.  From where had she spoken and how long ago?  <br>
<br>
Athene, troubled by ghosts and guilt, collected her things.  She was oddly tired and had a sudden yearning to return to the old guild tree.  Perhaps someone there—maybe Demitasse?—had received some news of Stormygale.  Perhaps just being within the sacred tree would help channel her thoughts.<br>
<br>
She sealed the envelope containing a letter to Quaras, pressing the wax down firmly with her wolf-head seal.  She had re-established contact with Quaras over the last few months, but a matter as complicated as Stormygale was something that needed to be discussed face-to-face or through extended correspondence.<br>
<br>
With the letter to Quaras sealed and addressed to the guild hall of the Claw, Athene cast the teleport that would take her closest to what for many years had been home.  <br>
<br>
~Home, Saphron~ her mind breathed, and then in a brief flash of light, she was gone. <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#141419><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub148.ezboard.com/bthewordsofnagafen.showUserPublicProfile?gid=stormygalewindrunner>Stormygale Windrunner</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.cpmission.com/graphics/icons/icon45.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoN Member</span><br>  Posts: 878<br> <font color=#7A8798>(7/21/03 1:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Fraud</span><hr size=1> She landed with a thump in the Glade of Surefall. As she had hoped there was no one about. She quickly cast innate camo and vanished. Just in time as two more travelers appeared just as she stepped back. Her luck was holding.<br>
<br>
She quietly ran through the glade and out into Qeynos hills where she remained camo'd and on foot until she zoned once more into West Karana. <br>
<br>
Here she had no choice. She called for Doom, and he instantly appeared looking rested an clean. &quot;Hello my love,&quot; Stormygale crooned. &quot;I see you are looking fit and rested. Did you have any luck with that mare?&quot;  Doom arched his neck and snorted, shaking his head back and forth, which Stormygale took to mean that he was still working on it. &quot;I have no doubts, my friend. No doubts at all. How could anyone resist you?&quot; She kissed his nose and then mounted up, and camo'd them both. &quot;Let us go to East Karana.&quot; And off they sped. <br>
<br>
They zoned into North Karana, ran through, and then she quietly held her invisible horse to a slow walk over the bridge into East Karana. There was no one sitting upon it, as there would have been in days past. The old world had become an empty world. But it was lucky for her, as even as slowly as they walked, there was no silencing the sound of hooves on the wood of the bridge. <br>
<br>
From there she turned him right and down the hill into the river. They swam. If anyone had picked up her scent, this would take care of it. Doom was a powerful swimmer, and fast. She kept her camo up and saw no one. <br>
<br>
Finally they arrived at the new destination. A hut, small but serviceable that stood out over the water near a large and noisy waterfall. There was no one in it and she bid Doom goodbye with another kiss and wishes for better luck with the mare. <br>
<br>
Stormygale climbed the ladder and entered the hut and stretched out after kicking off her soggy boots. The sound of the waterfall was soothing and relaxing. For the first time in a while, she felt at peace. she had always loved this spot. <br>
<br>
But there was an intrusion into her mind.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Stormygale... talk..won't... can help!&quot;  What was this rubbish? Ah, she knew. She hadn't had any brandy for a while. Well, she knew how to fix that and rummaged in a pack.<br>
<br>
 <p><b>Stormygale El`Orian</b><img border=0 src="http://www.cpmission.com/graphics/icons/icon45.gif" /></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#212128><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub148.ezboard.com/bthewordsofnagafen.showUserPublicProfile?gid=quarasshadowscythe>Quaras Shadowscythe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoN Member</span><br>  Posts: 950<br> <font color=#7A8798>(7/21/03 3:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Fraud</span><hr size=1> Quaras gazed out over the battlements of the great guild hall of the Claw of Nagafen and paced anxiously.  The guild hall -- an almost fortress like structure carved into the edge of the fiery cliffs -- captured like a fly in amber high over the turbulent pools of molten lava that flowed below.  The elderly halfling stared at the letter in his hand and the broken seal and continued to pace back and forth on the high parapets overlooking the molten sea.  Below, inside the teeming guild hall, the morning bells had begun to ring.  The monks had risen from the deep meditation and were practicing their skills, feigning death in the depths of the sparsely furnished practice rooms.  Many of the clerics had attended morning masses in the common chapel and had retired to their private chapels for contemplation and reflection among distant and varied gods.  The shamen -- assembled deep within their icy lair -- had shed the hibernation of a long evening sleep and were restlessly sharpening their claws and summoning their pets.  Quaras paced distractedly back and forth almost ignoring the thunderous plumes of magical energy emanating from the wizard's tower.  He remained focused on the letter from Athene -- an anxious letter from one who was not prone to anxiousness -- and cast his thoughts out to an empty part of the guild hall -- the small druid's grove.  &quot;Stormy has been gone for too long,&quot; he thought to himself.  &quot;What kind of trouble is the wee lass in now?&quot;<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#141419><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub148.ezboard.com/bthewordsofnagafen.showUserPublicProfile?gid=revil>Revil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoN Officer</span><br>  Posts: 1503<br> <font color=#7A8798>(7/21/03 7:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Fraud</span><hr size=1> Revil sitting, and waiting behind the wall hears the woman snort, and wake up after he made sure she was ok. The wee girl snored so loud after drink that brandy. He couldn’t concentrate on his task to lift her back into her bed, and cover her for the night from the late night chill Skyshrine gives off from it’s icy walls. Even though he knew she was out cold for a while. Revil took 10 platinum pieces from her purse quickly, and decided to mess with her even more after being ignored. Stacking the platinum pieces in the middle of the floor.<br>
<br>
After doing such a devious deed, he went back to his hiding spot and waiting till she woke up again. Not too long after he placed the 10 platinum pieces in the middle of the floor he hears the woman wake up. Slow, and groggy with a few groans here and there she takes a few sips of her almost empty bottle of brandy. Not too long after he hears a “whoosh”. So Revil peeks into the roam, and the woman is gone leaving only a particle trail to show she was once there.<br>
<br>
“I sure hope that woman is ok, and I didn’t scare her too much. She seemed so troubled before I even messed with her.”<br>
<br>
Revil slowly walks into the room seeing if there is anything he can salvage that she may have left behind. As he steps near the bed in the corner of his eye he sees a quick flash. He turns quickly in the direction of the flash with daggers posed, ready to attack any danger. Seeing no one there he relaxes his attack pose, and scans the room than looks towards the floor.<br>
<br>
“What is this?” Revil mutters<br>
<br>
Revil bends down to pick up a locket. Slowly scanning, and feeling the locket he feels some engraved words on the back. “Abruzi &amp; Loving daughter Stormygale” <br>
<br>
“She must have dropped this in her hurry to leave.” Revil grins.<br>
<br>
Revil slowly scans the locket more, and finds the button to open it. The picture inside is of a peck, and a girl. The girl in this picture must be at least 16 – 18 years of age at the time. Thinking to himself for a quick second. He can make a few plat off this locket, but than thinks about it some more, and decides to return the locket to its rightful owner. <br>
<br>
“Stormygale must be the name of that woman since she is too tall to be a peck. Guess it’s time to visit the Peckville again. Boy do I hate that place, and their munchkin music, but the food is the best in all the lands.” <br>
<br>
Revil stands back up, and hears footsteps of someone coming by. He quickly moves to teh nearest shadows making sure he is not seen. Seems one of the golems is carrying a peck into the room next door. He creeps to the archway, and makes sure his exit is clear. Slowly sneaking his way out of Skyshrine Revil starts his journey to Rivervale.<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=172191" target="top">Revil Nemessis</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->65th Shiza Riza of the Half-Breed Conspiracy<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->One pistol of a Rogue<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Disclaimer: Disgruntled for entertainment purposes only</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#212128><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub148.ezboard.com/bthewordsofnagafen.showUserPublicProfile?gid=athene>Athene</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.mindspring.com/~abvogan/_uimages/ahstarsm.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoN Member</span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#7A8798>(7/22/03 12:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=37>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.mindspring.com/~abvogan/eye.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Fraud</span><hr size=1> There was no one in the guild hall, but evidence of Demitasse’s continued residence was obvious.  The place was spotlessly clean, the kitchen was well stocked, a comfortable chair was pulled close by the fireplace hearth.<br>
<br>
Athene stowed her bags in the entry hall as was her custom and made her way to the room that had been Abruzi’s.  On one shelf an amazing collection of rare liqueurs still remained.  Athene considered, briefly, uncorking one and downing the whole lot; but she changed her mind.  She hated to drink alone.<br>
<br>
She sat on the small bed that had been Abruzi’s and studied the pictures on the bedside table.  Except for the two small portraits and a wood carving, the table was empty.  Athene studied the images lost in thought.  In one picture, a lovely, youngish Abruzi gazed out into the distance, … maybe into the future, defiantly full of confidence.  In the other, a very young Stormygale displayed all the complexities of adolescence.  She was captured neither smiling, nor frowning.  She was somewhere in between the conflicting emotions that had characterized her youth.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.mindspring.com/~abvogan/sitebuildercontent/sitebuilderpictures/saffyre2.jpeg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> <!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.mindspring.com/~abvogan/sitebuildercontent/sitebuilderpictures/stormy.jpeg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
It had been an accomplished artist Abruzi had commissioned to paint the likenesses, and Athene recalled that Abruzi had paid quite a large sum, for she had requested six portraitures actually—the two larger images that graced her bedside table, and four miniatures for two lockets … one for herself and the other for Stormygale. <br>
<br>
Athene felt incredibly sad for no real reason she could identify.  Abruzi had been gone for a long time.  Why was she so deeply saddened now?   Perhaps because not only was the mother lost, but now it seemed, the daughter as well.  Wherever she slumbered in her drunken stupor, deepened by fatigue and pain, Stormygale was conceivably miles from anyone.  She was miles from Athene, from Saphron, from those who still cared …  <br>
<br>
Athene continued to gaze at the portraits, studying the mother and daughter.  Though Stormygale had taken after her father’s people in stature and style, she and her mother shared the same nose, the same pursed lips.<br>
<br>
~I only want to talk, Stormy. I want to help.  Come back to the guild hall.  You know where of I speak.~<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub148.ezboard.com/bthewordsofnagafen.showUserPublicProfile?gid=athene>Athene</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.mindspring.com/~abvogan/_uimages/ahstarsm.gif" BORDER=0> at: 7/22/03 12:29 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#141419><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub148.ezboard.com/bthewordsofnagafen.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zyphindalcohol>Zyphin Dalcohol</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoN Member</span><br>  Posts: 1831<br> <font color=#7A8798>(7/22/03 1:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Fraud</span><hr size=1> As Zyphin sat in his family home stitching away on what was soon to become yet another piece of acrylia reinforced armor he pricked his finger with his needle.<br>
<br>
&quot;Tunare be damned!&quot; he exclaimed.<br>
<br>
&quot;Watch it mortal.&quot; exclaims a voice from out of nowhere.<br>
<br>
Zyphin having heard this voice before and knowing the import of it was quick to beg forgiveness.  &quot;Sorry, M'Lord.  How can this humble servent be of service to you.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;One of Tunare's faithfull has fallen and needs a hand. I am sending you to help her as you have been in similar straights.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes M'lord.  Where can I find this fallen Tunarean?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Look for her........silk.......waterfall&quot; as the voice breaks up as if being gagged.<br>
<br>
&quot;M'lord?&quot; ask Zyphin with a bit of aprehension. But nothing.  <br>
<br>
Zyphin is left with two very disturbing problems, first what has happened to his lord that would cause him to break off communication so abruptly and second who was this Tunarean he was supposed to help.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Well I can do nothing to help my lord at this time but maybe if I find and help this Tunarean I can plead an audiance with the Mother of All.&quot; Zyphin thinks as he twist his tunarean signet ring. <br>
<br>
So where to start? Zyphin was not given alot of clues only that he was looking for a female and that she had something to do with silk and a waterfall. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#212128><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub148.ezboard.com/bthewordsofnagafen.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sylvrwolf>SylvrWolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoN Member</span><br>  Posts: 239<br> <font color=#7A8798>(7/22/03 4:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.datamagick.com/images/dancing.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Fraud</span><hr size=1> Entering into Skyshrine, Kalyndria feels a sense of peace. The sentries acknowledge her, but say nothing as she passes silently through the halls. The Necromancer she followed here seems to have disappeared. &quot;Vandergrave....where did you go?!&quot;<br>
Closing her eyes, she tries to concentrate enough to ask her guild if there's been any more information on Stormygale, but she can't seem to communicate with most of them. &quot;Must be because of their affiliation with the Giants,&quot; she mutters. &quot;Bah!&quot;<br>
Passing into closer quarters, she comes across a couple of sentinels carrying what looks to be a halfling. She's broken and battered, and out cold. It takes Kalyndria a few moments to figure out where she's seen this particular halfling before. Once she does, she's even more upset. This is Saphron, one of Stormygale's friends, and a powerful healer.<br>
&quot;Oh no...Saphron...&quot; Following the sentinels, she watches them set her up in a room, placing her gently on the bed, and her things beside it. When they leave, she goes in and stands above her. &quot;Saphron, what happened to you?&quot;<br>
Gathering in her mind the healing knowledge she has acquired, she sets to the task of mending the broken halfling. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.users.bigpond.net.au/tamtam/kalyndria3.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
Base by <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.yumestudio.it/angychan/dolls/#" target="top">Angy chan</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <br>
<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#141419><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub148.ezboard.com/bthewordsofnagafen.showUserPublicProfile?gid=saphronlafeete>Saphron LaFeete</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoN Member</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#7A8798>(7/22/03 9:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Fraud</span><hr size=1> She winced in pain. The cloud of darkness was lifting now, and she was floating. The plains were so empty, save for the occasional giant spider or wandering lioness. She felt a shiver. Was she cold? Or just creeped out - those spiders . . . <br>
<br>
Wait . . . floating? Bah! She was dreaming. Why was she here, of all places? She had not been on the Karanas in ages, especially in her dreams. The plains stretched for miles beneath her. As she approached the river, she felt a feeling of familiarity. <br>
<br>
&quot;Look, she stirs!&quot; came a hissing from . . . somewhere behind her.<br>
<br>
She was falling. No! She wanted to see what this feeling of familiarity meant. She hated the Karanas. Why had the ether led her here?<br>
<br>
&quot;Saphron?&quot; came a soft voice, unknown to her, yet somewhat familiar.<br>
<br>
Light pierced the darkness as she strained to open her eyes. <br>
<br>
Had she had any energy at all she would have bolted for the door, for she was looking straight into the eyes of a great wyvern. <br>
<br>
&quot;Calm yourself, halfling,&quot; the gently wyvern hissed softly, &quot;It is I, Fardonad Fe'Dhar. You know me.&quot;<br>
<br>
Even though she was frightened, Saphron knew she would come to no harm. This was the wyvern who had bestowed upon her the blue armor of Veeshan.<br>
<br>
Beside the wyvern sat a lovely elven druid, a friend of Stormygale's from the Claw of Nagafen, if her clouded memory served her.<br>
<br>
&quot;What is your business in the Shrine?&quot; came a gruff voice from behind the two who had obviously been caring for her.<br>
<br>
&quot;Be still Commander Leuz! She came to us in search of a friend,&quot; the wyvern halted the drake's questioning with a wave of his clawed hand.<br>
<br>
&quot;Stormygale. Where is she? Is she here?&quot; Saphron managed.<br>
<br>
&quot;No, child, she has gone from us,&quot; came the reply in her mind.<br>
<br>
&quot;That human left quite a stench, too,&quot; Commander Leuz barked. &quot;It'll take my men a week to clear the smell of her liquor out of that room!&quot;<br>
<br>
The pain quickly subsided, and as the wyvern and the druid worked together, Saphron was able to stand.<br>
<br>
&quot;Thank you for your services my old friend,&quot; Saphron took the great wyvern's hand in hers, &quot;I appreciate you more than you know.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Thank the elf Kalyndria, as well. Her knowledge of the healing arts is great, and she has been very attentive. She, too, seeks your friend. Travel with her, Saphron, find that girl. She needs your help.&quot; <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:gold;font-family:Garamond;font-size:medium;">Saphron LaFeete</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--> <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:purple;font-family:garamond;font-size:small;">High Priestess of Bristlebane </span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.showMessageRange?topicID=142.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b> <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.showMessageRange?topicID=142.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.showMessageRange?topicID=142.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.showMessageRange?topicID=142.topic&start=81&stop=100>5</a><a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.showMessageRange?topicID=142.topic&start=101&stop=119>6</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.showPrevMessage?topicID=142.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.showNextMessage?topicID=142.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=40><img src=http://www.clawofnagafen.com/boards/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.emailToFriend?topicID=142.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.threadControl?topicID=142.topic><img src=http://www.clawofnagafen.com/boards/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=142.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=142.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub148.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thewordsofnagafentherunningcharterdiscussion">Charter<option value="thewordsofnagafengeneralmembersforum">General Discussion<option value="thewordsofnagafennewrecruits">New Recruits<option value="thewordsofnagafenmuirlansweeklypics">The Claw Tavern<option value="thewordsofnagafenmemberlist">Member List<option value="thewordsofnagafenfrm20">Good Deeds<option value="thewordsofnagafenimportantcurrentinformation">Important Current Information<option value="thewordsofnagafenmembersonlygeneraldiscussion">Members Only General Discussion<option value="thewordsofnagafenguildevents">Guild Events<option value